---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<div class="gr-home not-content">

<!-- ═══ HERO ═══ -->
<section class="gr-hero" id="gr-hero">
  <h1 class="gr-hero-headline">
    <span class="gr-stop-word">Stop</span>
    <span class="gr-flip-line" id="gr-verb-line">
      <span class="gr-flip-track" id="gr-verb-track"></span>
    </span>
    <span class="gr-flip-line" id="gr-noun-line">
      <span class="gr-flip-track" id="gr-noun-track"></span>
    </span>
  </h1>
  <p class="gr-hero-sub">
    You built automations that were supposed to help. Now they generate more noise than they filter. GraphReFly is the reactive graph engine that reduces chaos to signal — with every decision traceable and every node inspectable.
  </p>
  <div class="gr-hero-install" data-copy="npm i @graphrefly/graphrefly" title="Click to copy">
    <span class="gr-prompt">$</span>
    <span>npm i @graphrefly/graphrefly</span>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="gr-rule"></div>

<!-- ═══ HEADACHES ═══ -->
<section class="gr-headaches" id="gr-headaches">
  <div class="gr-headaches-header">
    <p class="gr-section-num">The Problem</p>
    <h2 class="gr-section-headline">Three headaches.</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="gr-headache-rows">
    <div class="gr-headache-row" data-index="0">
      <div class="gr-headache-pain">
        <svg class="gr-card-bg-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 2 7 12 12 22 7 12 2"/><polyline points="2 12 12 17 22 12"/><polyline points="2 17 12 22 22 17"/></svg>
        <div class="gr-headache-num">01</div>
        <h3 class="gr-headache-title">Volume Without Boundaries</h3>
        <p class="gr-headache-desc">Information multiplies across sources — email, Slack, feeds, APIs, logs. No single system sees it all. <strong>You become the integration layer.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="gr-headache-solution">
        <svg class="gr-card-bg-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="18" cy="5" r="3"/><circle cx="6" cy="12" r="3"/><circle cx="18" cy="19" r="3"/><line x1="8.59" y1="13.51" x2="15.42" y2="17.49"/><line x1="15.41" y1="6.51" x2="8.59" y2="10.49"/></svg>
        <p class="gr-solution-label">GraphReFly</p>
        <h3 class="gr-solution-title">Distributed Reactive Graphs</h3>
        <p class="gr-solution-desc">A single reactive topology connects every source. Distributed graphs federate across services. One graph sees what ten dashboards can't.</p>
        <div class="gr-solution-demo">Demo: Email Triage &rarr;</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gr-headache-row" data-index="1">
      <div class="gr-headache-pain">
        <svg class="gr-card-bg-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="10" x2="14" y1="2" y2="2"/><line x1="12" x2="15" y1="14" y2="11"/><circle cx="12" cy="14" r="8"/></svg>
        <div class="gr-headache-num">02</div>
        <h3 class="gr-headache-title">Velocity Without Rhythm</h3>
        <p class="gr-headache-desc">Markets move in milliseconds. Policies update quarterly. Emails arrive in bursts. Each source has its own clock — <strong>and your cron job missed the one that mattered.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="gr-headache-solution">
        <svg class="gr-card-bg-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="5" cy="19" r="1"/><path d="M4 4a16 16 0 0 1 16 16"/><path d="M4 11a9 9 0 0 1 9 9"/></svg>
        <p class="gr-solution-label">GraphReFly</p>
        <h3 class="gr-solution-title">Push-Based Propagation</h3>
        <p class="gr-solution-desc">Each node reacts the instant its source changes. No polling intervals. No missed beats. No stale snapshots accumulating in context.</p>
        <div class="gr-solution-demo">Demo: Spending Alerts &rarr;</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gr-headache-row" data-index="2">
      <div class="gr-headache-pain">
        <svg class="gr-card-bg-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m7 21-4.3-4.3c-1-1-1-2.5 0-3.4l9.6-9.6c1-1 2.5-1 3.4 0l5.6 5.6c1 1 1 2.5 0 3.4L13 21"/><path d="M22 21H7"/><path d="m5 11 9 9"/></svg>
        <div class="gr-headache-num">03</div>
        <h3 class="gr-headache-title">Action Without Memory</h3>
        <p class="gr-headache-desc">You vibe-coded a fix. It worked. Next month, nobody knows why — or whether it's still correct. <strong>Disposable solutions you can't repeat, explain, or build upon.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="gr-headache-solution">
        <svg class="gr-card-bg-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"/><path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"/></svg>
        <p class="gr-solution-label">GraphReFly</p>
        <h3 class="gr-solution-title">Persistent Causal Chain</h3>
        <p class="gr-solution-desc">Every decision traces back through a structural causal chain. Persistent, inspectable, composable. Change upstream — downstream knows it may no longer hold.</p>
        <div class="gr-solution-demo">Demo: Knowledge Graph &rarr;</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="gr-rule"></div>

<!-- ═══ PYRAMID ═══ -->
<section class="gr-requirements" id="gr-requirements">
  <p class="gr-section-num">The Vision</p>
  <h2 class="gr-section-headline">Four requirements.</h2>
  <p class="gr-requirements-intro">
    For human + LLM co-operation to work at scale, the system must satisfy all four. <strong>Miss one, the whole thing breaks.</strong>
  </p>

  <div class="gr-pyramid-wrap">
    <div class="gr-pyramid">
      <div class="gr-pyramid-tier">
        <div class="gr-pyramid-block" data-req="symmetry">
          <div class="gr-pyramid-block-title">Human / LLM Symmetry</div>
          <div class="gr-pyramid-block-sub">Either side composes, reviews, modifies</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gr-pyramid-tier"><div class="gr-pyramid-connector"></div></div>
      <div class="gr-pyramid-tier gr-pyramid-tier--pair">
        <div class="gr-pyramid-block" data-req="audit">
          <div class="gr-pyramid-block-title">Human Audit</div>
          <div class="gr-pyramid-block-sub">Every decision traceable</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gr-pyramid-block" data-req="creation">
          <div class="gr-pyramid-block-title">LLM-Safe Creation</div>
          <div class="gr-pyramid-block-sub">Constrained error space</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gr-pyramid-tier"><div class="gr-pyramid-connector"></div></div>
      <div class="gr-pyramid-tier">
        <div class="gr-pyramid-block" data-req="security">
          <div class="gr-pyramid-block-title">Security</div>
          <div class="gr-pyramid-block-sub">Per-node access control. Multi-tenant isolation.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gr-pyramid-detail" id="gr-pyramid-detail">
      <div class="gr-pyramid-detail-title" id="gr-detail-title">Click a block to explore</div>
      <div class="gr-pyramid-detail-body" id="gr-detail-body">
        Each requirement builds on the ones below. Security is the foundation — without it, nothing is trustworthy. LLM-safe creation and human audit sit in the middle — both require secure infrastructure. At the apex, human/LLM symmetry requires all three: safe creation, auditability, and enforced boundaries.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="gr-rule"></div>

<!-- ═══ SPEC ═══ -->
<section class="gr-core" id="gr-core">
  <p class="gr-section-num">The Spec</p>
  <h2 class="gr-section-headline">Five components.</h2>
  <p class="gr-requirements-intro" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
    The irreducible core. Remove any one and at least one requirement fails. <strong>Click them to see what breaks.</strong>
  </p>

  <div class="gr-core-graph">
    <div class="gr-core-row active" data-component="node">
      <div class="gr-core-toggle"><span class="gr-core-icon">&check;</span><span class="gr-core-name">node</span></div>
      <div class="gr-core-main">
        <div class="gr-core-content">
          <span class="gr-core-desc">Minimal compute unit with declared dependencies</span>
          <span class="gr-core-broken">LLM returns to writing arbitrary code. Error space is unbounded.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="gr-core-enables"><div class="gr-enables-stack"><span class="gr-enables-tag">LLM-Safe Creation</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="gr-core-row active" data-component="edge">
      <div class="gr-core-toggle"><span class="gr-core-icon">&check;</span><span class="gr-core-name">edge</span></div>
      <div class="gr-core-main">
        <div class="gr-core-content">
          <span class="gr-core-desc">Dependency as explicit data — the links between nodes</span>
          <span class="gr-core-broken">Dependencies are implicit. Causal chain breaks.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="gr-core-enables"><div class="gr-enables-stack"><span class="gr-enables-tag">Human Audit</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="gr-core-row active" data-component="propagation">
      <div class="gr-core-toggle"><span class="gr-core-icon">&check;</span><span class="gr-core-name">propagation</span></div>
      <div class="gr-core-main">
        <div class="gr-core-content">
          <span class="gr-core-desc">Change &rarr; downstream notified instantly, no stale state</span>
          <span class="gr-core-broken">Manual update coordination. Back to polling, back to vibe coding.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="gr-core-enables"><div class="gr-enables-stack"><span class="gr-enables-tag">LLM-Safe Creation</span><span class="gr-enables-tag">Human Audit</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="gr-core-row active" data-component="describe">
      <div class="gr-core-toggle"><span class="gr-core-icon">&check;</span><span class="gr-core-name">describe()</span></div>
      <div class="gr-core-main">
        <div class="gr-core-content">
          <span class="gr-core-desc">Structure visible, persistable, diffable at any moment</span>
          <span class="gr-core-broken">Structure is invisible. Not persistable, not diffable.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="gr-core-enables"><div class="gr-enables-stack"><span class="gr-enables-tag">Human Audit</span><span class="gr-enables-tag">Security</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="gr-core-row active" data-component="graphspec">
      <div class="gr-core-toggle"><span class="gr-core-icon">&check;</span><span class="gr-core-name">GraphSpec</span></div>
      <div class="gr-core-main">
        <div class="gr-core-content">
          <span class="gr-core-desc">Declarative, LLM-readable format for compose / review / modify</span>
          <span class="gr-core-broken">LLM can't structurally operate on the graph.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="gr-core-enables"><div class="gr-enables-stack"><span class="gr-enables-tag">Human / LLM Symmetry</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="gr-rule"></div>

<!-- ═══ CTA ═══ -->
<section class="gr-cta" id="gr-cta">
  <p class="gr-section-num">Ship It</p>
  <h2 class="gr-section-headline">It exists.</h2>
  <p class="gr-cta-sub">
    The TypeScript and Python implementations are live. Zero dependencies. Tree-shakeable. One primitive.
  </p>

  <div class="gr-cta-actions">
    <div class="gr-cta-card" data-copy="npm i @graphrefly/graphrefly">
      <p class="gr-cta-lang">TypeScript</p>
      <p class="gr-cta-cmd"><span class="gr-prompt">$ </span>npm i @graphrefly/graphrefly</p>
      <a href="https://github.com/graphrefly/graphrefly-ts" class="gr-cta-gh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View on GitHub &nearr;</a>
    </div>
    <div class="gr-cta-card" data-copy="pip install graphrefly">
      <p class="gr-cta-lang">Python</p>
      <p class="gr-cta-cmd"><span class="gr-prompt">$ </span>pip install graphrefly</p>
      <a href="https://github.com/graphrefly/graphrefly-py" class="gr-cta-gh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View on GitHub &nearr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="gr-rule"></div>

<!-- Footer -->
<footer class="gr-footer">
  <span class="gr-footer-logo">GraphReFly</span>
  <div class="gr-footer-links">
    <a href="https://github.com/graphrefly/graphrefly-ts">GitHub</a>
    <a href={`${base}spec/`}>Spec</a>
    <a href={`${base}api/node/`}>API</a>
  </div>
</footer>

<div class="gr-toast" id="gr-toast">Copied to clipboard</div>

</div>

<style is:global>
@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Sans:wght@400;700;900&family=Syne:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap");

/* ── Break out of Starlight wrappers ── */
.sl-markdown-content:has(.gr-home) { max-width: 100% !important; }
.content-panel:has(.gr-home) { max-width: 100% !important; padding: 0 !important; }
.content-panel:has(.gr-home) .sl-container { max-width: 100% !important; padding: 0 !important; }
.content-panel:has(.gr-home) .hero { display: none; }
.content-panel:has(.gr-home) > .sl-container > .sl-markdown-content { margin-top: 0 !important; }

/* Root also needs class `not-content` (Starlight): see markdown.css adjacent-sibling margin-top on .sl-markdown-content. */
.gr-home {
  --gr-black: #0a0a1a;
  --gr-white: #f0f4ff;
  --gr-accent: #c8ff00;
  --gr-red: #ff3b30;
  --gr-muted: rgba(240,244,255,0.5);
  --gr-muted-20: rgba(240,244,255,0.2);
  --gr-muted-10: rgba(240,244,255,0.1);
  --gr-muted-05: rgba(240,244,255,0.05);
  color: var(--gr-white);
  font-family: 'Syne', 'Plus Jakarta Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
  max-width: none; width: 100%;
}

.gr-home h1, .gr-home h2, .gr-home h3 {
  font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
  font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: -0.06em; line-height: 0.95;
  border: none !important; padding-top: 0 !important; margin-top: 0 !important;
}

.gr-home a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
.gr-rule { border-top: 4px solid var(--gr-white); }

.gr-section-num {
  font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 900;
  font-size: 1.1rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--gr-muted); margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.gr-section-headline {
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem); margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
}


/* ═══ HERO ═══ */
.gr-hero {
  min-height: 100vh;
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center;
  padding: calc(var(--sl-nav-height, 4rem) + 2rem) 2rem 4rem;
  max-width: 1400px; margin: 0 auto;
}

.gr-hero-headline {
  margin-bottom: 2rem; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.06em;
}

.gr-stop-word {
  display: block;
  font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--gr-red);
  font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 9vw, 9rem);
  line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 0.15em;
}

.gr-flip-line {
  display: block; position: relative; overflow: hidden;
  font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 900;
  text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.06em;
  font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 8rem); line-height: 1.15;
  height: calc(clamp(3rem, 8vw, 8rem) * 1.15);
}

.gr-flip-track {
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; will-change: transform;
}
.gr-flip-track.gr-animate { transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.23, 1, 0.32, 1); }
.gr-flip-track.gr-no-transition { transition: none !important; }

.gr-flip-item {
  flex-shrink: 0; display: flex; align-items: center;
  font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 900;
  text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.06em;
  font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 8rem); line-height: 1.15;
  height: calc(clamp(3rem, 8vw, 8rem) * 1.15);
  white-space: nowrap;
}

.gr-verb-word { color: var(--gr-accent); }
.gr-noun-word { color: var(--gr-white); }

.gr-hero-sub {
  max-width: 680px; font-size: 1rem; color: var(--gr-muted);
  margin-bottom: 2rem; line-height: 1.7;
}

.gr-hero-install {
  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.8rem;
  padding: 0.7rem 1.2rem; border: 2px solid var(--gr-white);
  font-family: 'Fira Code', 'SF Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.9rem;
  cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
}
.gr-hero-install:hover { background: var(--gr-accent); color: var(--gr-black); border-color: var(--gr-accent); }
.gr-prompt { color: var(--gr-muted); user-select: none; }
.gr-hero-install:hover .gr-prompt { color: var(--gr-black); opacity: 0.5; }


/* ═══ HEADACHES ═══ */
.gr-headaches {
  max-width: 1400px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 0;
  min-height: 100vh; display: flex; flex-direction: column;
}
.gr-headaches-header { padding: 0 2rem 2rem; }
.gr-headache-rows { flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }

.gr-headache-row {
  flex: 1; border-top: 2px solid var(--gr-muted-20);
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 0fr;
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: grid-template-columns 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.22, 0.61, 0.36, 1);
}
.gr-headache-row:last-child { border-bottom: 2px solid var(--gr-muted-20); }
.gr-headache-row.gr-revealed { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }

.gr-headache-pain {
  position: relative; overflow: hidden; z-index: 1;
  padding: 1.5rem 2rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: flex-start; min-width: 0; transition: background 0.8s;
}
.gr-headache-row.gr-revealed .gr-headache-pain { background: rgba(255,59,48,0.03); }

.gr-headache-num {
  font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 900;
  font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--gr-muted-20);
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase;
  transition: color 0.8s;
}
.gr-headache-row.gr-revealed .gr-headache-num { color: rgba(255,59,48,0.35); }

.gr-headache-title {
  font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.5vw, 1.8rem) !important;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em !important; margin-bottom: 0.5rem !important; line-height: 1.1 !important;
  transition: color 0.8s;
}
.gr-headache-row.gr-revealed .gr-headache-title { color: var(--gr-red) !important; }

.gr-headache-desc { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--gr-muted); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 520px; }
.gr-headache-desc strong { color: var(--gr-white); }

.gr-headache-solution {
  position: relative; overflow: hidden; z-index: 1;
  padding: 1.5rem 2rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: flex-start; background: var(--gr-accent); color: var(--gr-black);
  min-width: 0; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.5s 0.3s;
}
.gr-headache-row.gr-revealed .gr-headache-solution { opacity: 1; }

.gr-card-bg-icon {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 5%;
  right: 5%;
  width: 140px;
  height: 140px;
  opacity: 0.04;
  pointer-events: none;
  z-index: -1;
  transform: rotate(-10deg);
  transform-origin: center;
  transition: opacity 0.8s, transform 0.8s, color 0.8s;
}
.gr-headache-row.gr-revealed .gr-headache-pain .gr-card-bg-icon {
  opacity: 0.12;
  transform: rotate(0deg) scale(1.1);
  color: var(--gr-red);
}
.gr-headache-solution .gr-card-bg-icon {
  opacity: 0.1;
  transform: rotate(10deg);
}
.gr-headache-row.gr-revealed .gr-headache-solution .gr-card-bg-icon {
  opacity: 0.15;
  transform: rotate(0deg) scale(1.1);
}

.gr-solution-label {
  font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 900;
  font-size: 1.1rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem; opacity: 0.45;
}
.gr-solution-title {
  font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.5vw, 1.8rem) !important; color: var(--gr-black) !important;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em !important; margin-bottom: 0.5rem !important;
  line-height: 1.1 !important; white-space: nowrap;
}
.gr-solution-desc { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6; opacity: 0.75; max-width: 460px; }

.gr-solution-demo {
  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
  margin-top: 1rem; padding: 0.4rem 0.9rem;
  border: 2px solid var(--gr-black);
  font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 900;
  font-size: 0.7rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s; width: fit-content;
}
.gr-solution-demo:hover { background: var(--gr-black); color: var(--gr-accent); }


/* ═══ PYRAMID ═══ */
.gr-requirements {
  padding: 4rem 2rem 3rem; max-width: 1400px; margin: 0 auto;
  min-height: 100vh; display: flex; flex-direction: column;
}
.gr-requirements-intro {
  max-width: 720px; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--gr-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 2rem;
}
.gr-requirements-intro strong { color: var(--gr-white); }

.gr-pyramid-wrap {
  display: flex; gap: 3rem; max-width: 1100px; margin: 2rem auto 0;
  width: 100%; align-items: center;
}

.gr-pyramid {
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0;
  flex-shrink: 0; width: 520px;
}
/* Stretch every tier to the pyramid width so centered blocks share one column width. */
.gr-pyramid-tier {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: stretch;
  width: 100%;
  align-self: stretch;
}
.gr-pyramid-tier--pair {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  align-items: stretch;
  justify-items: stretch;
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 420px;
  margin-inline: auto;
  min-height: 0;
}
.gr-pyramid-tier:nth-child(1) { max-width: 280px; margin-inline: auto; }
.gr-pyramid-tier:nth-child(2) { max-width: 280px; margin-inline: auto; }
